A roll stabilising system according to the invention will now be described by way of example and with reference to the accompanying drawings, in which:


FIG. 1 is an hydraulic circuit diagram of a roll stabilising system according to the invention which also shows diagrammatically certain mechanical elements of the system;


FIG. 2 is a perspective view of certain of the mechanical elements shown in FIG. 1;


FIG. 3 is a block diagram showing an electronic control system used to control the hydraulic circuit shown in FIG. 1;


FIGS. 4 to 7 show part of the hydraulic circuit diagram shown in FIG. 1 in first, second, third and fourth operating modes respectively;


FIG. 8 is a graph showing vehicle roll angle plotted against vehicle lateral acceleration; and


FIG. 9 is a graph showing the restoring torque exerted by the roll stabilising system plotted against vehicle lateral acceleration.
